1 (2) (a) A child-care worker is eligible for the best beginnings child care scholarship program if the
2 worker:
3
4 (A) is employed at a licensed day-care center or registered family or group day-care home and is
5 engaged in any of the eligible activities, FOR AT LEAST THE MINIMUM NUMBER OF HOURS REQUIRED as established
6 by the department pursuant to 45 CFR 98.16(g), for at least the required minimum number of hours ; AND
7 (B) HAS A HOUSEHOLD INCOME THAT IS LESS THAN TWO TIMES THE STATE MEDIAN INCOME.
8
9 (b) The income eligibility requirements provided in subsection (1) do not apply to a child-care
10 worker who is otherwise eligible under this subsection (2)."
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Appropriation. There is appropriated $5.5 million from the general fund
13 to the department of public health and human services for each year of the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for
14 the purposes of providing best beginnings child care scholarships to eligible child-care workers as provided in
15 [section 1].
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
